definitions.definition: A tip , originally of metal and often decorative, on a ribbon or cord that makes lacing two parts of a garment or garments together easier, as in corset lacings , " points " (lacing hose or trousers to jacket or doublet) or sleeves to a bodice .
An ornament worn on clothing, consisting of a metal tag on a fringe, or a small metallic plate or spangle.
